Police are appealing for witnesses after a four-year-old girl was injured in a hit-and-run.She was treated in hospital for minor injuries after the incident, which happened on Rochester Drive, Ellesmere Port in Cheshire on Thursday just before 16:30 BST.The girl has since been discharged.Police are appealing for witnesses after the driver of a black car failed to stop, and made off towards Thornton Road.A Cheshire Police spokesman said enquiries were ongoing and appealed to anyone who witnessed the collision or has dashcam footage or CCTV footage to contact the force.
